reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Thick, soft, premium diapers
reviews.reviewText: Over the past few years we have a used a variety of diapers. We have used and tried diapers from Pampers, Huggies, Luvs, Hello Bello, The Honest Company and All Good. At the moment we are using Pampers Cruisers 360 and Pampers Swaddlers Overnights; sometimes we use Pampers Pull-Ups.From the moment, I opened the package, it was clear these were premium diapers. They are thick and soft. One of children (2 years old) said they felt comfy. Overall, I'd say these diapers are great!The diapers are sized differently from what I'm used to. I typically buy size 4 but based on Terra sizing we needed the size 5. They looked a little big to me - just something to be mindful of. Even though these diapers are thicker, they are still easy to tear on the sides. I found the absorbency to mostly be comparable to the Pampers. We did have a few (loose) poop leaks that went through the diaper but not onto clothes. We also had one pee leak although the diaper didn't seem that full and had only been worn for ~3 hours but I feel that was just a weird thing.
